  <refnamediv>
    <refname>imdecorrstretch</refname>
    <refpurpose>Apply decorrelation stretch to multichannel image</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   S = imdecorrstretch(I, tol, useCorr)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>I :</term>
      <listitem><para> Input image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>tol :</term>
      <listitem><para>  The fraction of the image to saturate at low and high intensities. If tol is an scalar, high intensity is 1 - tol.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>useCorr :</term>
      <listitem><para> 1 to use correlation method, 0 to use covariance method.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>S :</term>
      <listitem><para> Stretched output image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The primary purpose of decorrelation stretch is visual enhancement. Decorrelation stretching is a way to enhance the color differences in an image.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
S = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/" + 'baboon.png'));
S2 = imdecorrstretch(S);
subplot(121);imshow(S);
subplot(122);imshow(S2);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

